TwoFactorTempCode.name: TwoFactorTempCode
TwoFactorTempCode.description: Stores information about a user’s temporary verification code for confirming their identity when logging in.

Expiration.description: The date and time when the temporary verification code expires. The code expires in 1 to 24 hours after it’s generated. Salesforce admins and non-admin users with the Manage Multi-Factor Authentication in User Interface permission set the expiration time when generating the code.

Identifier.description: The unique identifier for the temporary code. This is a required field that can take any value.

UserId.description: The ID for the user who’s associated with the temporary verification code.
